Delay Report

September 17, 2024

Delay Report for Dengue

There were 5992 enrollees diagnosed with Dengue.

The diagnostic opportunity window (i.e., time period before diagnosis where diagnostic opportunities may occur) was set between 1 and 30 days before diagnosis.

Visit Trends

Potential diagnostic opportunities: During the diagnostic opportunity window there were 9945 total patient visit days (i.e., days when a patient encountered the healthcare system), and of these visit days 4475 represented SSD-visit days (i.e., days where a patient presented with signs, symptoms or symptomatically similar diseases to Dengue).

The following is a plot of all patient visits and SSD-related visits that occurred in the 180 days prior to the index Dengue diagnosis.

SSD Visit Results

Expected Visit Trends

The following figure depicts the estimated trends in the number of expected visit counts (red line) for SSD-related visits compared to the observed number (black line). The dashed line represents the start of the diagnostic opportunity window. Plots are presented using linear, quadratic, cubic and exponential models to fit the expected number of SSD-related visits each day before the diagnostic opportunity window.

The following table summarizes the observed and expected number of visits and the estimated number of missed opportunities using each of the four different models plotted above:

model Total Visits Expected Visits Number Missed
cubic 4423 1855 2568
exponential 4423 1652 2771
linear 4423 1263 3160
quadratic 4423 1549 2874

The following plot describes the estimated number of missed opportunities each day before the index diagnosis using each of the four models described above:

The final selected model (based on model fit prior to the diagnostic opportunity window) was the cubic model with an estimated number of missed opportunities of 2568

Bootstrapping Results

The following section summarizes results of the bootstrapping analysis where the individual specific visits representing a diagnostic delay were repeatedly sampled. A total of 1000 trials were run for this analysis (100 outer bootstraps and 10 trials inside each bootstrap sample)
